What is BeeGFS?

BeeGFS is a distributed file system that provides high performance, high availability, and scalability. It is designed to be used in a cluster of nodes, each of which has its own storage. The BeeGFS cluster is made up of a master node and one or more worker nodes. The master node is responsible for managing the cluster, including allocating storage and coordinating access to it. The worker nodes are responsible for storing and serving data, and they communicate with the master node through a network.

What is Federated Learning?

Federated Learning is a distributed machine learning framework that allows multiple parties to train a machine learning model without sharing any data.

The parties can be mobile devices, IoT devices, or any other device that has access to data.

The parties can be located in different geographical locations, and the model can be trained in real-time.

The parties can also be connected to a central server, which can provide the model training and updates.
